> They don't log anything outside of internal debug messages

This was determined by searching their codebase for uses of `logging.getLogger` (used in 6 places). They assign their logger to the variable `log`. Searching for `log.error`, `log.warning`, and `log.error` returned no results. Searching for `log.debug` returned 5 results, none of which log anything returned from the Docker API. Only internal messages.

@troyready - if you want me to try submitting a PR upstream I can but given the above it probably won't go anywhere. Just trying to prevent this from being a blocker here or in the docker-py repo. I can remove the logging completely if it's an issue. It's just not as "user friendly" especially for long running builds with a lot of steps (or those of us that panic a little when the terminal stops providing feedback for more than 3 seconds) as the terminal will just sit there and not be able to provide feedback until the `docker image build` action is complete.

